#Approach:

💡 IDEA
- Queue ko actually maintain karne ki zaroorat nahi hai.
- Sirf left aur right boundary track karo.

Initially:

[1,2,3,4,5,...,N]

Left person = i
Right person = j

- Kabhi first K log tickets lete hain.
- Kabhi last K log tickets lete hain.
- Ticket milne ke baad log queue se remove ho jaate hain.

- Isliye bas pointers shrink karte raho.

⚙️ APPROACH
1. i = 1 (front)
   j = N (back)

2. flag maintain karo:
   true  → front se remove
   false → back se remove

3. K log remove karo.

4. K removals complete hone ke baad:
   - Direction change karo.
   - Counter reset karo.

5. Jab i == j:
   - Sirf ek person bacha hai.
   - Wahi answer hai.

📝 EXAMPLE

N = 9
K = 3

Initial:

[1,2,3,4,5,6,7,8,9]

i = 1
j = 9

--------------------------------

Front se 3 remove

1 removed
2 removed
3 removed

i = 4

Remaining:

[4,5,6,7,8,9]

--------------------------------

Back se 3 remove

9 removed
8 removed
7 removed

j = 6

Remaining:

[4,5,6]

--------------------------------

Front se 3 remove

4 removed
5 removed

Now:

i = j = 6

Answer = 6

✅

------------------------------------------------

N = 5
K = 1

[1,2,3,4,5]

Remove 1

[2,3,4,5]

Remove 5

[2,3,4]

Remove 2

[3,4]

Remove 4

[3]

Answer = 3

✅

❓ WHY TWO POINTERS
- Actual queue operations unnecessary hain.
- Log sirf front ya back se remove ho rahe hain.
- Beech ke logon ki relative position matter nahi karti.

Isliye:

Front removal → i++
Back removal  → j--

Bas boundaries maintain karna enough hai.

⏱️ COMPLEXITY
Time  : O(N)

Reason:
- Har person exactly ek baar remove hota hai.

Space : O(1)

🎯 INTERVIEW POINT
- Queue tag misleading hai.
- Queue banane ki zaroorat hi nahi.

- Key observation:

  Sirf dono ends se removals ho rahe hain.

- Therefore:

  Queue Simulation → O(N) space

  Two Pointers → O(1) space

- Most important variables:

  i    → current front person
  j    → current back person
  flag → kis side se ticket distribute ho raha hai

- This is actually a Two Pointer Simulation problem disguised as a Queue problem.

#Code:

public class Solution {
    public static int distributeTicket(int N,int K) {
        //You can code here

        int i = 1;
        int j = N;
        boolean flag = true;
        int cnt = K;
        while(i <= j){
          
          if(i == j){
            return i;
          }

          if(flag){
            i++;
            cnt--;
          }
          else{
            j--;
            cnt--;
          }

          if(cnt == 0){
            cnt = K;
            flag = (!flag);
          }
        }
        return 1;        
    }
}
